      scope: "Authored IT-06 (+63 LOC): `#[tokio::test] it_06_fetch_metadata_requests_latest_is_release_not_prerelease` added to pre-existing tests/pypi_index_client_integration.rs (shipped tick 72 shard-3b commit f2e0da96 with IT-01..IT-05). Test calls `client.fetch_metadata(\"requests\")` (JSON primary path), takes versions[0] (sorted newest-first by pub(crate) sort_versions_newest_first via simple_api.rs:53), asserts latest is NOT pre-release (byte-level scan for aN/bN/rcN suffix immediately after a digit) AND NOT dev-release (.dev substring check). Scoped as integration-only, zero production touches. Gated under `#[cfg(feature = \"integration\")]` per pre-existing convention. **Initial draft** used `fetch_metadata_simple(\"requests\")` but hit a parser-layer bug — pypi.org /simple/requests/ serializes `yanked` as PEP 691 §3.2 string-reason ('Yanked due to conflicts with CVE-2024-35195 mitigation') but pkgmgr/simple_api.rs deserializes strict-bool, yielding ParseError 'invalid type: string ..., expected a boolean'. **Pivoted to fetch_metadata** (JSON primary + Simple fallback, JSON path unaffected by the bug); added explicit NOTE comment in IT-06 documenting the workaround. **Verification**: `cargo test -p mamba --features integration -- --test-threads=1 it_06` → 1/1 pass in 0.56s against live pypi.org. 4TH PM-correction-pattern at AC level (AC1/129, AC3/133, AC5/137, AC2/153) — baseline-grep pre-dispatch confirmed tests/pypi_index_client_integration.rs already existed with IT-01..IT-05 from tick 72; AC2 wording 'live-PyPI integration test to be authored' was stale at filing. Pivoted from full authoring to semantic-lock augmentation (IT-06 locks the literal AC2 assertion: latest is release, not pre/dev)."
