    - slug: bug-mamba-raise-silently-swallowed-on-user-exception-subclass-with-super-init
      change_id: impl-direct-raise-swallow-hypothesis-g   # SDD bypass — direct impl-direct for well-scoped 1-LOC fix
      scope: "1-LOC `unsafe { super::rc::retain_if_ptr(instance); }` at projects/mamba/src/runtime/class.rs:2219 inside pub fn mb_super, before `fields.insert('__super_self__'.to_string(), instance);`. Symmetric to b8596bf7 pattern (retain pairs with JIT Return-terminator I64 vreg release). Root cause: super_proxy held a non-retained ref to instance via __super_self__; when JIT __init__'s Return released super_proxy vreg, its fields-drop auto-released the non-retained ref, dropping instance rc 1→0 before mb_raise_instance dereferenced. Fix mirrors b8596bf7 exactly. Also added projects/mamba/tests/fixtures/conformance/exceptions/super_init_raise.py (20 lines, AppError(Exception) subclass with super().__init__(msg) + self.code + raise/catch + post-init attribute survival) + .expected (4 lines). custom.py fixture now prints all 5 expected lines (was 3/5)."
